Rating: 4
This was fabulous, but I made a few changes: First, I used 3/4 of a recipe of the "Best Ever Pie Crust" from July 2007 Bon Appetit, which tastes great and made enough to double up the crust around the edges. Then I borrowed a technique from an old pecan pie recipe I have and boiled dark corn syrup for a few minutes before adding it to the egg, which helped everything set nicely in the oven. One of the other cooks remarked that her pecans were soggy, but this technique made them nice and glazed and crisp. You have to keep a close eye on the syrup, taking it on and off the flame to keep it from boiling over, and then stream it into the egg very slowly, whisking the whole time, but it's worth it. I also added a splash of bourbon to the sweet potatoes, and if I were to make this recipe again (I hope I get the opportunity) I would use half again as much sweet potato, but keep the amount of spices the same. So delicious!

