Rating: 0
To clarify what the previous poster from New York said, Bon Appetit knows that sweet potatoes are not "true" yams (a true yam is a starchy tuber with flesh the color of that of a regular potato and not sweet at all, from the southern hemisphere). BA lists "red-skinned sweet potatoes (yams)" beacause while sweet potatoes are not botanically yams, most people in the US call the orange-fleshed sweet potatoes yams and refer to the yellow-fleshed ones as sweet potatoes.

Rating: 2
Thanks to the previous reviewer for clarifying that this recipe uses a regular sweet potato, NOT a yam! I made this pie for Thanksgiving and I got a lot of compliments. I don't know if they were trying to be nice or if I'm just finicky, but I wasn't crazy about it. I did not care for the texture. The spicy flavor of the sweet potato base was delicious and even the topping was tasty, but the nuts on top were very soft & chewy, whereas I expected them to be firm. Maybe I overcooked it or my oven was too hot. I don't know if this is the way the nuts are supposed to be...

